info.description: The iconic front man of Australian Crawl talks through the far reaching music of his life.
info.title: James Reyne gets musically reckless with Chris Bath for the Evenings Music Teacher

text.markdown:
Image: 

Supplied

#  Music Teacher - James Reyne

On Evenings with Chris Bath 

[Download James Reyne gets musically reckless with Chris Bath for the Evenings Music Teacher (18.92 MB)](https://abcmedia.akamaized.net/radio/local_sydney/audio/201901/aaw-2019-01-22-james-reyne-music-teacher.mp3)

Download 18.92 MB

You'll know James Reyne as the lead singer of Australian Crawl. You might even remember his debut on Countdown with two broken arms. 

What you might not know that he was born in Nigeria, loves Gilbert & Sullivan, and hates most 80s music! 

Listen to him here as he takes you through the influential songs of his life. The ones he loves, hates, and everything in between. 

Duration: 41min 19sec 

Broadcast:  Tue 22 Jan 2019, 7:00pm
